5. Memory Allocation in Stack Vs Memory allocation in Heap

Program memory Parts - Text segment , (PCB) ,Data segment , Heap , Stack  , OS Kernel
   
   5.a Stack - once scope of variable/function/class is complete , corresponding stack is destroyed and memory is freed. 
           Stack memory limit is less (...MB) , if stack height keeps increasing and is beyond the limit , it causes stack overflow
           and program crashes.
           
   5.b Heap - Dynamic memory allocation at runtime . RAII - 
              New & Delete 
              Smart Pointers - Automatic memory management 
                             - Unique , Shared , Weak smart pointers
                             
